<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 84.</note>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. E. B. Washburne</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[By cable.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-09-14"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 14, 1870</date>. (Received. September
                                14.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Paris making stupendous preparations for defense. Three hundred thousand
                            soldiers in city. Slight hopes of negotiations through England.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WASHBURNE.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>